Title: Reagan Promises to Veto Welfare Reform Without Work Requirement
 President Reagan warned Saturday that he will veto any welfare legislation Congress sends him that does not contain a work requirement
Downey D NY in the Democrats response said that quiring welfare recipients work may be necessary but he said such requirements should be controlled by state and local welfare officials not the federal government
Reagan mingled talk of welfare reform with celebration of his administration s economic record saying Friday s unemployment figures showed that the jobless rate hovered just above the lowest it s been in 14 years
